        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title><supplied reason="lost">Numbers 5</supplied><ref n="1"
                                target="#Num-005-fn1_trl" type="noteAnchor" /></title>
                        <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Num005-P217r-L15_trl" n="15"
                            prev="ADub.III.73.004.004.trl.xml#Num004-P217r-L15_trl" />
                        <l n="1">And the Lord spoke
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             to Moses, saying,</l>
                        <l n="2">‘Command the children of Israel,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             that they shall drive out of the camp every leper, and everyone who has
                            a discharge,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             and everyone who is unclean by a soul.</l>
                        <l n="3">From male to female:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             you shall drive |them| outside the camp; you shall drive them, and they
                            shall not make
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             their camps, in the midst of which my divine Presence
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             dwells, unclean.’</l>
                        <l n="4">And the
                            <milestone unit="page" n="217v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             children of Israel did so, and drove them out, outside the camp.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             As the Lord spoke to Moses, so did the children of Israel.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                        <l n="5">And the Lord spoke to Moses, saying,</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                        <l n="6">‘Speak to the children of Israel, “A man or a woman
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             who commits any of the sins of humans, to do a trespass
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             against the Lord: and if that soul is guilty,</l>
                        <l n="7">Then they shall confess
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             their sin which they have done. And he shall pay back
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             for his trespass wholly, and ha shall add to it its fifth part,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             and he shall give it to him against whom he has trespassed.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                        <l n="8">But if the man has no kinsman to pay him back
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             for the trespass, the trespass that is payed back is the Lord’s,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             for the priest, besides the ram of the atonement by which
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             he will ask for atonement for him.</l>
                        <l n="9">And every heave offering
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             of all the holy things of the children of Israel which they bring
                            forward to the priest,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             shall be his.</l>
                        <l n="10">And a man’s holy things
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             shall be his possession. Whatever a man wants to give to a priest
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             shall be his.’</l>
                        <l n="11">And the Lord spoke to Moses,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             saying,</l>
                        <l n="12">‘Speak to the children of Israel, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             you shall say to them, ‘Any man whose wife go astray and does a
                            trespass:</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                        <l n="13">And if a man lies with her — an intercourse
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             of seed — and this thing is hidden from the eyes of her husband, and
                            <milestone unit="page" n="218r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             if she is hidden and becomes unclean, and if there is no witness
                            against her,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             and she was not been caught,</l>
                        <l n="14">And if the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             thought of jealousy overflows him, and he is jealous of his wife, and
                            she became unclean,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             or if the thought of jealousy comes through him, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             she did not become unclean:</l>
                        <l n="15">Then the man shall bring
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             his wife to the priest, and he shall bring her offering
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             for her, the tenth part of an ephah of barley flour.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             He shall not pour oil on it and shall not put
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             frankincense on it, because it is a grain offering of jealousy, a grain
                            offering
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             of remembrance, causing an iniquity to be recalled.</l>
                        <l n="16">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             the priest shall bring her forward and stand her before the Lord.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                        <l n="17">And the priest shall take holy water in an earthen vessel,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             and the priest shall take of the dust that is in the floor of the
                            tabernacle
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             and put it into the water.</l>
                        <l n="18">And the priest shall stand
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             the woman before the Lord and uncover
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             the woman’s head and put the grain offering of remembrance in her
                            hands:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             it is the grain offering of jealousy.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             And in the hands of the priest there shall be bitter
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             cursing water.</l>
                        <l n="19">And the priest shall make her take an oath,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             and say <delSpan spanTo="#Num-005-del001_trl" />to her<anchor
                                type="delSpan" xml:id="Num-005-del001_trl" />
                            <addSpan spanTo="#Num-005-add001_trl" /><emph>to the woman</emph><anchor
                                type="addSpan" xml:id="Num-005-add001_trl" />, ‘If no man has lain
                            with you, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             if you have not gone astray to uncleanness |while you were| under your
                            husband’s authority,
                            <milestone unit="page" n="218v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             you shall be innocent from his bitter water that causes the curse.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                        <l n="20">But you, if you have gone astray |while| being under your
                            husband’s authority,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             and if you have become unclean, and if
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             a man other than your husband has given you his bed,’</l>
                        <l n="21">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             Then the priest shall make the woman to take an oath
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             of this curse, and the priest shall say to the woman, ‘May the Lord
                            give you
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             a curse and an oath among your people when the Lord sets
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             your thigh sagging and your womb swelling.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                        <l n="22">And this <addSpan spanTo="#Num-005-add002_trl"
                                 /><emph>curs</emph><supplied reason="lost"
                                ><emph>ing</emph></supplied><anchor type="addSpan"
                                xml:id="Num-005-add002_trl" /> water shall go in your insides,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             to swell the womb and make the thigh sag.’
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             And the woman shall say, ‘Amen, amen.’</l>
                        <l n="23">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             the priest shall write these curses in a book, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                             he shall rub them into the bitter water.</l>
                        <l n="24">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                             he shall cause the woman to drink the bitter cursing water and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                             the bitter cursing water will come into her, to become bitterness.</l>
                        <l n="25">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                             And the priest shall take grain offering of jealousy out of the woman’s
                            hand,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                             and shall wave the grain offering before
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                             the Lord, and he shall bring it forward to the altar.</l>
                        <l n="26">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                             the priest separate from the grain offering its incense, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                             shall burn it on the altar, and afterward he shall make the woman drink
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                             the water.</l>
                        <l n="27">And he shall make her drink
                            <milestone unit="page" n="219r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                             the water, and it shall be: if she was unclean,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                             and has trespassed a trespass against her husband,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                             the cursing water will come into her, to become bitterness, and her
                            womb will swell,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                             and her thigh will sag, and the woman shall be a curse among
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                             her people.</l>
                        <l n="28">And if the woman has not been made unclean,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                             and she is clean, and she will be innocent and shall conceive seed
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                             from the bitter water.</l>
                        <l n="29">This is the teaching of jealousies,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                             when a wife goes astray being under her husband’s authority
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                             and becomes unclean.</l>
                        <l n="30">Or if the thought of jealousy overflows a man,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                             and he is jealous over his wife,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                             and he shall stand the woman before the Lord,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                             and the priest shall do of this teaching to her.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                        <l n="31">And the man shall be innocent from iniquity, and that woman
                            <milestone unit="line" xml:id="Num005-P219r-L14_trl" n="14"
                                next="ADub.III.73.004.006.trl.xml#Num006-P219r-L14_trl" />
                             shall bear her punishment.</l>
                    </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
